%% JWT Auth Flow (Access + Refresh)
flowchart TD
  A[Client] -->|POST /api/auth/login| B[AuthController]
  B --> C[AuthService.login]
  C -->|validate credentials| D[UserRepository]
  C -->|create tokens| E[JwtService]
  E -->|access token| F[Access Token]
  E -->|refresh token| G[Refresh Token]
  C -->|store hashed refresh| H[RefreshTokenRepository]
  C --> I[AuthenticatedUserDto]
  I -->|access+refresh| A

  %% Access token usage
  A -->|API request + Authorization: Bearer access| J[JWT Auth Filter]
  J -->|validate access token| E
  J -->|set user context| K[Protected Controller]

  %% Refresh flow
  A -->|POST /api/auth/refresh + refresh token| L[AuthController]
  L --> M[AuthService.refresh]
  M -->|validate refresh token| E
  M -->|verify stored hashed| H
  M -->|rotate refresh token| H
  M -->|issue new access+refresh| E
  M --> N[AuthenticatedUserDto]
  N --> A

  %% Logout
  A -->|POST /api/auth/logout + refresh token| O[AuthController]
  O --> P[AuthService.logout]
  P -->|delete stored hashed| H
